    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Messages in the Killing of Hussein's Sons</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Maggie K Nelson letter asks why Saddam Hussein's sons were not put on trial rather than killed</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''The Brothers Grim'' (editorial, July 23):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''The Brothers Grim'' (editorial, July 23):</p>
        <p>If our goal as a country is truly to promote justice and democracy, shouldn't even the most vile of criminals, like these two men, be arrested and put on trial?</p>
        <p>Wouldn't this have been a better example and a beginning to establishing the rule of law in Iraq, rather than sending in troops to assassinate them?</p>
        <p>These are Saddam-style tactics, and frankly, I am ashamed. I think that the Iraqi people deserved to see these two men on trial, facing their accusers.</p>
        <p>MAGGIE K. NELSON  Minneapolis, July 23, 2003</p>
      </block>
